SRS Aviation founding member and Director, Sibongile Sambo will continue to give testimony at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture in Parktown, Johannesburg on Wednesday. The commission will this week hear the second round of aviation-related testimonies. Sambo gave background to her business and details on how she became the owner of SRS,Â  the first 100% female black, owned aviation company. SRS provides jets and helicopter rental services to both local and private customers. Sambo will continue to give testimony and elaborate further on how her relationship with South African Airways and the contracts she entered into. Before starting her testimony this week, Sambo told Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo that she was suffering from depression and would sometimes forget the sequence of evets but would talk through what she remembers. Click below to watch related videos: